CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper January 24, 1953, pg. 30, reads: "Celebration of YMCA Week Starts This Saturday - Developing Grace - Under the leadership of Fred Malone, a group lets itself out a[illegible] some interpretive dancing, designed to develop grace and charm and to build stronger, healthier bodies. This is a splendid outlet for Y-lean girls. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of one male, possibly Victor Hereford, and four female dancers wearing dance costumes posed in Centre Avenue YMCA
